extends ../_.pug
append head
	title= mena
block body
	h1= mena
	p #{mena} is a record of the culture of #{fokra}; the people that worship #{dolita}.
	p No one worships the entirety of #{dolita}, but rather the Deities important to their life.
	details#professions
		summary Professions
		ul
			li
				| Cooks:
				ul: li= deity.brainur
			li
				| Hunters:
				ul
					li= deity.djur
					li= deity.strefnur
					li= deity.nokvur
			li
				| Inventors:
				ul
					li= deity.opfin
					li= deity.grendur
					li= deity.skopkin
			li
				| Scientists:
				ul
					li= deity.efkimin
					li= deity.golgemin
					li= deity.sirilur
					li= deity.upgodin
					li= deity.grendur
			li
				| Smiths:
				ul
					li= deity.kufnur
					li= deity.nokvur
			li
				| Wizard:
				ul
					li Any mortal can become a Wizard, but some people are more gifted than others
					li There are post-secondary schools, where one can become a skilled wizard
					li
						| Imbued by #{deity.galdin}, with a fraction of the power of another Deity; i.e:
						ul
							li Pyrokinetics; #{deity.bradur}
							li Hydrokinetics; #{deity.vadin}
							li Geokinetics; #{deity.jodur}
							li Anemokinetics; #{deity.ludin}
							li Electrokinetics; #{deity.eldur}
			li
				| Military:
				ul
					li
						| All combatants worship #{deity.stridur}
						ul
							li
								| Archer & Crossbowman:
								ul: li= deity.nokvur
							li
								| Mage:
								ul
									li A Wizard fighting in the military; specializing in combat-related magic
									li the deity of their chosen magic & #{deity.galdin}
							li
								| Rifleman:
								ul
									li= deity.nokvur
									li= deity.bisur
							li Swordsman:
					li
						| Medic:
						ul
							li= deity.skurdin
							li= deity.mecur
							li= deity.fridin
							li
								| Some medics are healing mages
								ul: li= deity.lakbin
	details
		summary#doda= doda
		p
			| #{doda} are a doomsday cult that worships #{deity.dodur}, believing their faith will spare them from The#{space}
			a(href="istaga.html#furda")= furda
			| .